    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1867-05-17T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1867-05-17T00:00:00-05:00" n="279" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d279">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                                Campbell</persName>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 27.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State,</hi>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington,</hi>
                        </placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1867-05-17">
                            <hi rend="italic">May</hi> 17, 1867</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> Your despatch No. 27, of 24th April last,
                            has been received, containing an account of your prompt despatch of a
                            messenger to President Juarez of <pb facs="0477" n="407" xml:id="pg_407"/> Mexico, and the reasons why he proceeded by the overland mail route
                            to San Luis Potosi.</p>
                <p>The alacrity with which you executed the instructions from this
                            department is deemed highly commendable.</p>
                <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lewis D. Campbell,</hi> Esq., <hi rend="italic">&amp;c., &amp;c., New Orleans.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
